HOUSE BILL NO. 3091 By: Dobrinski
5
6
7 PROPOSED POLICY COMMITTEE SUBSTITUTE
8 An Act relating to counties and county officers;
requiring elected county officials to maintain
9 principal residence for a minimum of eighty percent
of their term; clarifying failure to do so is
10 dereliction of duty; permitting the county
commissioners and district attorneys to remove
11 noncompliant officers; providing for codification;
and providing an effective date.
12
13
14 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
15 SECTION 1. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
16 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 131.2 of Title 19, unless there
17 is created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
18 Any elected county official in the State of Oklahoma shall
19 maintain a principal residence within their jurisdiction and occupy
20 that principal residence for a minimum of seventy percent (70%) of
21 their term. Failure to comply with this section shall qualify as
22 dereliction of duty by the elected county official and the county
23 commissioners and the district attorney may begin proceedings to
24 remove the elected county official from office. For purposes of
Req. No. 16119 Page 1

1 this section, "principal residence" shall have the same meaning as
2 defined in Section 131.1 of this title.
3 SECTION 2. This act shall become effective November 1, 2026.
